</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29414C13FF974B6FFF7FFE66FA1C24A1" blockId="42.[151,1437,438,861]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
The species is unrecognizable from 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFDE3FE66FD722799" author="Say, T." box="[603,746,475,501]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="149 - 178" refId="ref36174" refString="Say, T. (1829) Descriptions of North American dipterous insects. Journal Philadelphia Academia of Science, 6, 149 - 178." type="journal article" year="1829">Say’s (1829)</bibRefCitation>
original description of a single female from “ 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF974B6FFB52FE66FADD2799" box="[1258,1349,475,501]" name="Mexico" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Mexico</collectingCountry>
” and as with many of Thomas Say’s 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF974B6FFE6EFE42FD8C2475" box="[470,532,511,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">types</typeStatus>
, the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF974B6FFDFFFE42FDEF2475" box="[583,631,511,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
of this species may be lost or destroyed; the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF974B6FFBD3FE42FB072475" box="[1131,1183,511,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
(s) of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFB65FE42FAAD2475" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1829" box="[1245,1333,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFB65FE42FAAD2475" box="[1245,1333,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">P. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not found at 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF974B6FFF44FD9EFEDC2451" box="[252,324,547,573]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">ANSP</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF974B6FFEE8FD9EFE3F2451" box="[336,423,547,573]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">BMNH</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF974B6FFE0BFD9EFD9A2451" box="[435,514,547,573]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">MZHF</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF974B6FFDB6FD9EFDF22451" box="[526,618,547,573]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" type="Museum">NHMW</collectionCode>
, or 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF974B6FFD2EFD9EFD772451" box="[662,751,547,573]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">OXUM</collectionCode>
. According to a historical account of Say’s collecting trip to 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF974B6FFF2FFDFAFF75240D" box="[151,237,583,609]" name="Mexico" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFF44FDFAFDF2240D" author="Papavero, N. &amp; Ibanez-Bernal, S." box="[252,618,583,609]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="65 - 173" refId="ref35703" refString="Papavero, N. &amp; Ibanez-Bernal, S. (2001) Contributions to a History of Mexican Dipterology. Part I. Entomologists and their Works before the Biologia Centrali-Americana. Acta Zoologica Mexicana, New Series, 84, 65 - 173. [2001]" type="journal article" year="2001">Papavero &amp; Ibáñez-Bernal 2001</bibRefCitation>
and references therein), “Say, in the company of William McLure, travelled and collected along the old road between 
<collectingRegion id="EB3A82F1FF974B6FFD1BFDD6FC9224E9" box="[675,778,619,645]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
, Jalapa, 
<collectingRegion id="EB3A82F1FF974B6FFCD0FDD6FC6D24E9" box="[872,1013,619,645]" country="Mexico" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Mexico City</collectingRegion>
, and Tacuba, beginning in the autumn of 1827; and on the approach of summer (1828) they returned to the 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF974B6FFC36FD32FBB124C5" box="[910,1065,655,681]" name="United States of America" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">United States</collectingCountry>
.” While this account helps to narrow down the location of the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF974B6FFE59FD0EFD8924A1" box="[481,529,691,717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFD29FD0EFD7224A1" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1829" box="[657,746,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFD29FD0EFD7224A1" box="[657,746,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">P. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, several species of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFC7DFD0EFBA324A1" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[965,1083,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFC7DFD0EFBA324A1" box="[965,1083,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in this area of 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF974B6FFA9FFD0EFA1824A1" box="[1319,1408,691,717]" name="Mexico" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29414C13FF974B6FFF7FFD6AFD052531" blockId="42.[151,1437,438,861]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">
The species was not mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFDF5FD6AFD60249D" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[589,760,726,753]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref33819" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy’s (1945)</bibRefCitation>
work on the Neotropical species though the name was later included in Neotropical catalogs (
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFDA8FD46FD022579" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[528,666,762,789]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="437 - 476" refId="ref33931" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1959) Catalogue of the Neotropical Bibionidae. Acta Zoologica Lilloana, 17, 437 - 476." type="journal article" year="1959">Hardy 1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFD1DFD46FD46257A" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[677,734,763,790]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref34086" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1966) Family Bibionidae. In: Papavero, N. (Ed.), A Catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas South of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia da Secretaria da Agricultura do Estado de S &quot; o Paulo, S &quot; o Paulo, pp. 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
) and other regional lists of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFBAAFD46FAC22579" authority="(Fitzgerald 2000)" baseAuthorityName="Fitzgerald" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[1042,1370,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Bibionidae (
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFB23FD46FACA2579" author="Fitzgerald, S. J." box="[1179,1362,763,789]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="627 - 634" refId="ref33125" refString="Fitzgerald, S. J. (2000) Bibionidae. In: Llorente Bousquets, J. E., Gonzalez Soriano, E. &amp; Papavero, N. (Eds.), Biodiversidad, Taxonomia y Biogeograpfia de Artropodos de Mexico. Vol. II. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico, pp. 627 - 634." type="book chapter" year="2000">Fitzgerald 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Considering that this species is unrecognizable from the original description and the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF974B6FFBAEFCA2FBDE2555" box="[1046,1094,799,825]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">type</typeStatus>
could not be found, 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFA93FCA2FA1B2555" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1829" box="[1323,1411,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFA93FCA2FA1B2555" box="[1323,1411,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">P. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here treated as unrecognized (
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFE5FFCFEFD152531" box="[487,653,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">nomen dubium</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
